x4freetext: OBSERVATION OF TWO-HOLE STATES AT HIGH EXCITATION
ENERGY IN (P,T) REACTIONS.

x4codes.hlp: Hiroshima Univ., Hiroshima and Higashi-Hiroshima, Japan

x4freetext: .SOME CORRECTIONS IN THE DATA-SECTION.

x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Nuclear Physics, Section A, Vol.376, p.513 (1982)

x4freetext: THE UNCERTAINTY IN THE ABSOLUTE CROSS SECTIONS IS
ESTIMATED TO BE WITHIN 30 PER CENT.THIS IS AUTHOR`S
OPINION.
.SEE ABOVE.
/BY AUTHORS/.AN ENERGY SPECTRUM IN THE (P,T) REACTION
WOULD,FOR EXCITATION ENERGIES UP TO APPROX. 20 MEV,
CONSIST OF THREE PARTS.THE FIRST PART,CORRESPONDS TO
THE LEVELS NEAR THE GROUND STATE AND IS EXCITED BY
PICKING UP TWO NEUTRONS FROM VALENCE SHELLS AROUND THE
FERMI SURFACE.THE SECOND PART,ARISES FROM THE PICKUP OF
TWO NEUTRONS,ONE OF WHICH IS PICKED UP FROM A VALENCE
SHELL AND THE OTHER FROM A DEEP MAJOR SHELL.THESE HOLE-
STATE STRENGTHS ARE CONSIDERED TO POPULATE WIDELY IN
EXCITATION.THE THIRD PART IS A DEEP TWO-NEUTRON HOLE
STATE BASED ON THE PICKUP OF TWO NEUTRONS FROM A DEEP
MAJOR SHELL BELONGING TO THE INNER CORE.THERE HOLE
STATES ARE EXPECTED TO BE BROAD AND CENTRED AROUND AN
EXCITATION ENERGY WHICH IS ABOUT TWICE AS LARGE AS THAT
OF THE DEEP ONE-NEUTRON HOLE STATES.
ANGULAR DISTRIBUTIONS FOR THE BUMPS WERE MEASURED IN
THE ND-146(P,T)ND-144,ZR-94(P,T)ZR-92 AND ZN-68(P,T)
REACTIONS AT LABORATORY ANGLES BETWEEN 6 AND ABOUT 60
DEGREES.
.FIGURES QUALITY IN THIS PAPER IS SECOND-RATE.
NEGATIVE NUMBER IN DATA-SECTION IS RESULT OF FIGURES
QUALITY.
